, ecologists, and evolutionary biologists) because of their close associations with flowering plants and because of the ability of certain species to produce silk for nest building--an intriguing case of convergent evolution. For these readers, and for students of natural history and proponents of species preservation, The Pollen Wasps will prove an invaluable resource.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMasarinés. 0aPollen waspsxEcologyzAfrica, Southern. 0aPollen waspsxEcology. 0aPollen waspszAfrica, Southern. 0aPollen wasps. 0aTiere (Zoologie). 4aPollen wasps -- Africa, Southern. 4aPollen wasps -- Ecology -- Africa, Southern. 4aPollen wasps -- Ecology. 4aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution. 4aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Zoology / Entomology. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Science eBook Packagez9783110353549oZDB-23-HSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067428169140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067428168440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674281684423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674281684.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HSP